Class Positioned

  • java.lang.Object
    • rottapeli.domain.superclasses.Entity
      • rottapeli.domain.superclasses.Positioned
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Border, Cheese, Moveable, PlacementBlocker, Tail

    public class Positioned
extends Entity
    Entity that can be positioned.

    Extend this class when implementing an Entity that is drawn or has coordinates and dimensions.

    Author:
    Pavel

      • getNearbyPositions

        public void getNearbyPositions(Deque<Double> xQueue,
                      Deque<Double> yQueue,
                      List<Double> usedX,
                      List<Double> usedY)
        Enqueues coordinates above, below, left and right of the current coordinate. Doesn't do anything if current position is out of bounds or current position has been checked for near coordinates already.
        Parameters:
        xQueue - Queue of the X coordinates.
        yQueue - Queue of the Y coordinates.
        usedX - X coordinates that have been checked already.
        usedY - Y coordinates that have been checked already.

      • draw

        public void draw(Graphics g,
        double offsetX,
        double offsetY,
        double xMultiplier,
        double yMultiplier)
        Contains instructions on how to represent this entity in the GameField.

        If not overriden draws a black rectangle.

        Parameters:
        g - Graphics data.
        offsetX - X position of the drawing field in respect to window's location.
        offsetY - Y position of the drawing field in respect to window's location.
        xMultiplier - Horizontal stretching based on window's width.
        yMultiplier - Vertical stretching based on window's height.
